content.html: Society: “autistic people are so rigid and never consider others”. Autistic me: *habitually sacrifices my wants, needs, preferences and methodologies, and hides a huge and important part of my identity - to the detriment of my own health - to make other people feel comfortable*.
content.value:
Society: “autistic people are so rigid and never consider others”.

Autistic me: *habitually sacrifices my wants, needs, preferences and methodologies, and hides a huge and important part of my identity - to the detriment of my own health - to make other people feel comfortable*.
